SO-101 3D model assets
======================

The robot model shipped by this example (examples/so101/model/so101.urdf and
the STL meshes fetched at setup time by so101_setup.py) is derived from:

    The Robot Studio — SO-ARM100 / SO-101
    https://github.com/TheRobotStudio/SO-ARM100
    Pinned commit: fda892cba81032c46c40976a48c9ceadbf40a9ca
    Path:          Simulation/SO101/
    License:       Apache License 2.0

The URDF committed here (so101.urdf) is the upstream so101_new_calib.urdf with a
single mechanical change: every <mesh> reference was flattened from the upstream
"assets/<file>.stl" subdirectory path to a bare sibling "<file>.stl" name, so the
references resolve against Gantry's flat /models/ store. No geometry, joints,
limits, or inertials were altered.

The STL meshes are NOT redistributed in this repository. so101_setup.py downloads
each one directly from the pinned upstream commit and verifies its SHA-256 against
MANIFEST.json before uploading it to your bench.

Apache-2.0 requires that this attribution and the upstream license accompany
redistribution. The full license text is available at:

    https://github.com/TheRobotStudio/SO-ARM100/blob/fda892cba81032c46c40976a48c9ceadbf40a9ca/LICENSE
    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

